[Overall, there appears to be significant progress towards the goal of polio eradication, with numbers of reported cases markedly reduced from last year and all prior years since the initiative began. That being said, the occurrence of 2 cases of paralytic disease related to WPV1 that has most likely been in circulation undetected for the past 5 years in Borno, Nigeria is a major setback -- highlighting the challenges presented by areas with civil unrest and disruption of the health infrastructure in these regions. In the case of Nigeria, as previously noted, the affected area is the area considered to be where insurgents are sequestered, and normal activities such as vaccination have been seriously disrupted. Other areas similar to this exist elsewhere in the world, and one can't help but view declarations of WPV transmission interruption in such areas cautiously.

A very sad state of affairs when public health measures have been interrupted and blocked due to political and civil unrest.

A map showing the worldwide distribution of polio cases can be found at http://www.polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring/Poliothisweek/Poliocasesworldwide.aspx. - Mod.MPP]
